@startuml
title Optimisation Retrial Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User / OEX /\nAuthorised Platform" as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
database "OC MS DB" as OCDB
queue "OC MS Outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Python/Gurobi\nWorker" as Worker

== Retrial Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. POST /optimisation/{id}/retrial\n(If-Match header)
OGW -> OSB : 2-3. Invoke OSB MS\n<mTLS + User Context JWT>
OSB -> OSB : 4. Validate user context & runtime state\nExpose retrial action only if allowed
OSB -> NGW : 5. Forward retrial request\n<mTLS + OAuth2 (system-to-system)>
NGW -> OCMS : 6. Route retrial request

== Validation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 7. Validate original Optimisation\nlifecycleStatus = FAILED
OCDB --> OCMS : FAILED status confirmed

== New Optimisation Creation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 8. Create new Optimisation resource
note right of OCDB
  9. New Optimisation links to original\n   via retrialOf reference
  10. lifecycleStatus = ACKNOWLEDGED
end note
OCDB --> OCMS : New Optimisation persisted

== Event Publishing ==

OCMS -> Outbox : 11. Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\n(instruction = EXECUTE) for new Optimisation\n— same transaction
Outbox -> Kafka : 12. Relay publishes event to Kafka

== Worker Execution ==

Kafka -> Worker : 13. Python/Gurobi Worker consumes\nand processes new request

== Retrial Boundary ==

note over OCMS, OCDB
  14. Original FAILED Optimisation remains FAILED.
  Retrial does NOT move it back to PROCESSING.
  Only the new Optimisation progresses through the lifecycle.
end note

@enduml
